						               													<description>Where have both hedgehogs holed up? Where have the two fish disappeared to, and where is the pair of bears? To find out, concentration and a good memory are required in Mini-Memo. The player who can best remember the same pictures and therefore collect the most card pairs wins. A fun and colorful memory game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player whose turn it is turns over  two memory cards, one after the other.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Do they show the same picture?&amp;#10;Excellent! Keep these two memory cards. You may then turn over two more cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Do they show different pictures?&amp;#10;What a pity! After everyone has seen the memory cards, turn them back over again.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends when all the cards have been turned over and therefore all the pairs have been found. Stack your own memory cards. Whoever can build the highest card tower wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
